      • onConnected

        void onConnected(long total,
               boolean isRangeSupport)

        if ConnectTaskImpl is successfully connected with the http/https server this method will be invoke. If not method onFailed(DownloadException) will be invoke.

        Parameters:
        total - The length of the file. See URLConnection.getContentLength()
        isRangeSupport - indicate whether download can be resumed from pause. See ConnectTaskImpl.run(). If the value of http header field Accept-Ranges is bytes the value of isRangeSupport is true else false

      • onProgress

        void onProgress(long finished,
              long total,
              int progress)

        progress callback.

        Parameters:
        finished - the downloaded length of the file
        total - the total length of the file same value with method
        progress - the percent of progress (finished/total)*100
